A man has appeared in court after a teenager was allegedly sexually assaulted on a cycle path. Man in court over cycle path 'sex assault' A man has appeared in court after a teenager was allegedly sexually assaulted on a cycle path.The attack on the 18-year-old happened on the track between Johnstone and Linwood in Renfrewshire last Thursday.Sean Moynihan, 30, appeared in private at Paisley Sheriff Court.He was charged with sexual assault and also faces another charge of assault with intent to rob.Moynihan, from Paisley, made no plea and was remanded in custody.He is expected to return to court within eight days. 